review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-11.
Pours clear, golden with white head. Yeasty aroma - classical wheat beer notes very up front. Cloves, banana, wheat. Taste is slightly salty - not particularly bitter. Overall its a decent wheat. Nothing special, but quite drinkable.

Tasted 2015-06-11.
Poured semi clear amber. Scent of pumpernickel bread and pine cones. Very pleasant. Moderately bitter. A Little toffee. Overall very balanced and drinkable.
beer_name: Adnams Jack Brand Crystal Rye IPA

review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-11.
Normally Im, a big fan of heavy stouts and Amager Bryghus in general, however this one was off from the fizz. A very metallic scent straight from the cap left the bottle that dominated everything. Like drinking a liquified, old, rusty lawn mower. Barely drinkable. Bad bottle? I dunno? But it WAS drain pour.

Tasted 2015-06-11.
Pours clear Brown with bronze head. Moderately carbonated. Well balanced notes of coffee, roasted malts, liquorice and prunes. Not a big porter, but pleasant.
beer_name: De Jyske Bryghuse Viva La Vida In Riga

review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-11.
Pours clear, amber with white head. Bread-ish scent with hops pushed into the background. Slightly lactic notes. Not bitter enough to be called APA. A Little disappointing, though definately drinkable.
beer_name: Det Lille Bryggeri RBC Amar er No 1

review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-10.
Pours semi clear, amber with off white head. Powerful hop aroma. Grassy but pleasant. Very bitter taste with toffee and bread hidden a bit. Overall very good.

Tasted 2015-06-10.
Pours unclear amber with hop sediments. Not pretty, but it makes up for it in aroma and taste. Hops are upfront, and they linger on for a long time. Balanced bitterness/sweetness. Very drinkable but yet very distinct hoppiness. Overall a very nice beer.

Tasted 2015-06-09.
Pours unclear amber with little head. Aroma of orange and yeast. Slightly bitter taste. Too little hops for the style. Seems a bit green to be honest. Not great.

Tasted 2015-06-08.
Pours semi clear Brown. Fresh hoppy aroma. Toffee, cookie, pines. Moderately bitter. Very pleasant.

Tasted 2015-06-08.
Pours Black with bronze head. Flavour is dominated by raw liquorice. Especially in the finish, which is moderately bitter. Coffee, chocolate and bread is also present. Very powerfull yet very drinkable.

Tasted 2015-06-08.
Clear golden - almost amber - colour. No head whatsoever. Seems filtered. Nutty, hoppy aroma. Slightly bready. Only lightly carbonated. Very little bitterness for an IPA. A little on the boozy side. Overall pleasant and drinkable, but I expect more from an IPA at 6.7% ABV.

Tasted 2015-06-08.
Pours clear, golden with white head. Citrussy aroma with hints of pineapple and grass. Grassy hoppy finish. Mouthfeel on the watery side. Overall pleasant and very drinkable.
beer_name: Beer Here / Ugly Duck Helmuth Kellerbier

review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-08.
Clear, golden beer with white head. Pleasant hoppy aroma. Ditto taste with slightly bitter finish. Last sip is a little bland, but overall a very fine pale ale.
beer_name: Adnams Jack Brand Mosaic Pale Ale

review_blob:
Tasted 2015-06-08.
Crisp, clear, golden appearance with white, pearly head. Pleasant, fruity aroma with a clear lack of hops. Interestingly not a particular problem. I do think that just a tiny amount of hops could have served it well, but the brewer has certainly managed to create a hopless beer that is in fact very much still a (tasty) beer. Nice acid from the berries. Overall a well rounded beer.

Tasted 2011-08-01. Pours clear golden with white head. Not particularly wheaty. No real yeasty esters. Kinda blant actually. Decent bitterness, and no off flavours though. Drinkable, but boring relative to the price.
Tasted 2011-07-31. Pours clear, orange/amber with beige head. Piney, hoppy toffee aroma. Slightly yeasty start. Bitter finnish. Very pleasant. Very drinkable. Very fresh.
Tasted 2011-06-10. Pours dark brown with beige head. Aroma of coffee, roasted malt and cocoa. Slightly bitter and salty taste. Well balanced. Liked it.

Tasted 2011-06-09. This one was 2 years old in the bottle. Some oxidation, cellar scent, dusty. Still rather pleasant in its overly boozed taste. I didnt enjoy it, but I didnt expect to. Its an interesting experiment, and its clearly very well done, but for me, its way over the top.

Tasted 2011-06-07. Pours clear, chestnut with beige head. Piney, hoppy scent. Fast disappearing molases taste followed by strong bitterness. Seems more like a roasted bitterness than a hop bitterness. Not impressing IMO, but its drinkable.
beer_name: rbk B2 Dark IPA Limited Edition

review_blob: Tasted 2011-05-??. Pours red with off-white head. Raspberry aroma. Very tart but sweet. Decent.
Tasted 2011-05-20. Pours light amber with beige head. Aroma: smoked meat. Taste: Smoky, wheat, slightly bitter. Interesting beer. Kinda baconish. I enjoyed it.

Tasted 2011-05-19. Pours dark brown with beige head. Aroma: Coffee, roasted malts, smoked meat. Taste: salty, almost no bitterness, surprisingly rather sweet in stead. Nok one of my favourites, but OK.
Tasted 2011-05-19. Pours hazy, amber with beige head. Aroa is hoppy in a sorta soapish way. Its not as bad as it sounds. Its full bodied with a bitter finish. Very balanced.
Tasted 2011-05-19. Pours clear, red/brown with beige head. Aroma of hops and candis. Weak malt profile, but decent considering the ABV. Slightly bitter finish. Pretty good.

Tasted 2011-05-03. Pours clear, dark brown with no head. Aroma of rye bread, brown sugar and coffee. Taste is salty and slightly bitter with an aftertaste of maple syrup. Medium carbonation. Kinda watery. All in all pretty decent.
Tasted 2011-04-22. Pours muddy, dark red. Funky brett aroma. Some cherries. Not much. Sour. More funky than the raspberry version. Love it.
Tasted 2011-04-22. Pours morning urine colored with a white head. Aroma is citrussy hopped. Fresh taste. Not bitter. On the weak side. OK beer.
Tasted 2011-04-22. Pours clear yellow with white head. Aroma: Honney - somewhat nausiating. Taste is blant. I gues its decent considering the ABV, but there are a lot better NA beers out there.
Tasted 2011-04-??. Pours muddy, dark brown. Aroma of candis, port, cocoa and plums. Cloves are in the aftertaste. Some bitternes, but not much. Not too heavy. I like that.
Tasted 2011-04-??. Pours unclear urin-yellow with white head. Fresh malts, banana, citrus. Slightly bitter.
Tasted 2011-04-30. Pours thick amber with beige head. Aroma of yeast, cloves and banana. Slightly bitter taste. Full bodied. A little on the heavy side.
Tasted 2011-05-01. Pours clear, amber (dark) with beige head. Aroma of apples, prunes, caramel and cocoa. Taste is slightly bitter. A little salty. Medium carbonation. Decent, but uninteresting.
Tasted 2011-04-23. Pours clear, yellow with white head. Corn-ish aroma. Salty taste with bitter finish. Not bad. Not interesting.
Tasted 2011-04-26. Pours clear, light amber/golden/orange with no head. Metallic, malty aroma. Ditto flavours. Taste is mildly bitter. Uninteresting, but drinkable.

Tasted 2011-04-24. Pours clear, yellow with white head. Very light looking. Very clean. Too clean. Aroma is weak with just a hint of corn and metal. Taste is almost abscent. Like tap water that has been sitting all day in the pipes. This is borderline false marketing (calling it Danish Draught).
Tasted 2011-04-21. Pours dark brown with light brown head. Aroma of cookies, sour dough, raspberries. Taste is acidic and slightly bitter. Very full bodied. Very tasty.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Tasted 2011-04-21. Pours hazy straw yellow with white head. Cloves, banana, vanilla. Sweet without being nausiating. Rich, full bodied. Great.
Tasted 2011-04-23. Pours clear, amber with beige head. Aroma of metal and hops. Weak tasting. Slightly bitter. Soft carbonation. Its not one Ill return to.
Tasted 2011-04-21. Pours klar, dark amber with beige head. Aroma of sweet malts, basement and a bit of metal. Ever so slightly bitter finish. A bit on weak side, but decent.

Tasted 2011-04-20. Pours unclear, red/brown with pink head. Color is kind of earl grey tea-ish. Aroma of raspberries and bretts. Acidic taste, but not as funky, as one could expect. Very drinkable. Love it!

Tasted 2011-04-20. Pours hazy, straw yellow with white head. Banana, apples, cloves. Sweet initially with a bitter finish. There is a hit of diacetyl, that I dont care for. Reminiscent of a wheat beer.
Tasted 2011-04-20. Pours clear, amber with off-white head. Toffee, hops (few), nuts. A bit sweet and slightly bitter. OK beer.

Tasted 2011-04-18. Pours semi clear orange with white head. Slightly perfumed aroma; hops, grape fruit. Taste is lime, malt with a slightly bitter finish. Overall pretty watery. A bit of a disappointment coming from Mikkeller, but in general a decent brew.
Tasted 2011-04-18. Pours amber with beige head. Slightly hopped. Semi sweet, malty. OK, but a bit boring.
Tasted 2011-04-14. Pours hazy, pale yellow with off-white head. Notes of citrus, elderflower and sweet malts. Slightly bitter finish. Decent, actually.

Tasted 2011-04-19. Pours clear, light amber with beige head. Notes of walnuts, toffee and sweet bread. Slightly alcoholic. No bitternes to speak of. Usually I dont much care for these flavours, but it kinda works for this one.
Tasted 2011-04-18. As Green Easter. Pours hazy, amber with off white head.Harsh hoppy aroma with pineapples, Powerfully bitter taste. Decent, but a tad too harsh for my liking.

Tasted 2011-04-18. As my 600th rating I chose this, the best non-alc beer, weve been able to find (the wife is preggy, so shes off the hard stuff). It pours unclear, brown/orange with off white head. It has a very hoppy aroma with notes of toffee. It has a rather weak taste, but still its quite tasty. Moderately bitter finish. Even though its a bit watery, it actually ranks up there with some of the good, boozed ones for me. Thumbs up!
Tasted 2011-04-18. Pours chestnut brown with beige head. Nutty aroma, brown sugar, slightly metallic. Taste is a little acidic - no bitterness. Pretty decent beer.

Tasted 2011-04-17. Pours clear, amber with small, white head. A bit artificial looking. Piney hop scent. Very rich taste; initially sweet with a bitter finish. Pretty decent, but not particularly interesting.
